From ab071783d45d7b704eab54a43b135d53785392a1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xie Xiaodong <xiexiaodong16@huawei.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Apr 2026 09:58:54 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] PCI/ACPI: Support ITS selection for PCI VF devices

hulk inclusion
category: feature
bugzilla: https://atomgit.com/openeuler/kernel/issues/8916

----------------------------------------

Allow a PF to configure the ITS raw indices that should be used by its
VFs through sriov_vf_its_indices. Each VF resolves its target ITS from
that PF-provided list and uses the selected ITS MSI domain when
ACPI/IORT looks up the PCI MSI domain.

Add the PCI and IORT helpers needed to support this flow: store and
parse the PF-provided indices, resolve a VF-specific ITS index,
validate the configured indices against the PF ITS, and reject
configurations that are unsupported by the platform topology or ITS
implementation. This also exposes the ITS IIDR needed for the platform
support check and updates the platform ITS base-address map used during
validation.

Keep the validation and selection logs needed to diagnose
configuration issues, but the main change is enabling controlled ITS
selection for PCI VF devices.

Signed-off-by: Xie Xiaodong <xiexiaodong16@huawei.com>
